a trireme ( derived from latin : triremisfrom tri- " three " + remus " oar " . " with three banks of oars ; "   triērēs,from τρι- ( tri- ) " three " + ἐρέτης " rower " literally " three - rower " ) was an ancient vessel and a type of galley that was used by the ancient maritime civilizations of the mediterranean , especially the phoenicians , ancient greeks and romans .

ships : in the names bireme , trireme , & quarireme , " reme " refers to these

oars